# SaaS Starter Cursor Rules

## Core Features
- Authentication: Email/password + OAuth (Google, GitHub)
- Authorization: Role-based (Admin, Member, Viewer)
- Billing: Stripe Checkout + Customer Portal
- Dashboard: Analytics, settings, team management

## Auth Architecture
- Use NextAuth.js v5, Clerk, or Supabase Auth
- Implement email verification flow
- Support team/organization accounts
- Session-based auth for web, JWT for API

## Billing (Stripe)
- Use Stripe Checkout for payment flow
- Use webhooks for subscription lifecycle events
- Implement Customer Portal for self-service billing
- Gates: Check subscription status before premium features
- Handle edge cases: failed payments, trial expiry, plan changes

## Database Schema Patterns
- Users → Organizations (many-to-many via memberships)
- Organizations → Subscriptions (one-to-one)
- Feature flags tied to subscription plans
- Audit log for sensitive actions

## Dashboard
- Overview page with key metrics
- Settings: profile, team, billing, API keys
- Activity feed for recent actions
- Responsive layout with collapsible sidebar

## Security
- CSRF protection on all forms
- Rate limiting on auth endpoints
- Input sanitization and validation
- Webhook signature verification for Stripe
- API key authentication for programmatic access
